Components are stand-alone sets of Automation configuration that can be used by Automation and other modules on your site. Components are for example useful if you want to use the same conditions, actions or automation in multiple places, or call them from your custom module. You may also export each component separately. See the online documentation for more information about how to use components.
Control all configurations regardless of permission restrictions of events, conditions or actions.

React on events and conditionally evaluate actions.

Reaction automation associate one or more reactions to one or more specific site events. Execution of a workflow event actions can optionally be tied to one or more conditions. To list and update existing reaction automation and to create a new one, visit the reaction automation overview page.

Reaction automation, listed below, react on selected events on the site. Each workflow event may fire any number of actions, and may have any number of conditions that must be met for the actions to be executed. You can also set up components ‚Äì stand-alone sets of Automation configuration that can be used in Automation and other parts of your site. See the online documentation for an introduction on how to use social_automation.

The Automation module allows site administrators to define conditionally executed actions based on occurring events (ECA-automation). For more information, see the online documentation for the Automation module and the current Automation documentation for Drupal 8 on Gitbooks.
The Automation modules allows to set global settings settings, such as logging. Visit the automation settings page to view and update current settings.

The data selector helps you drill down into the available data. To make entity fields appear in the data selector, you may have to use the condition 'entity has field' (or 'content is of type'). More useful tips about data selection is available in the online documentation.

Workflow event components allows to define reusable combined actions which can optionally be tied to one or more conditions. Components are usable as actions in reaction automation or in other components. To list and update existing workflowevent components and to create a new one, visit the components overview pages.
Workflow event evaluation is triggered whenever the selected event occurs.
